        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 29 at 8:18PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 818 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Silver, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Silver and Sanco.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
